description:
What: Add /dm <handle> <text> slash command to cli/src/commands.rs that sends a point-to-point Whisper to a single peer.

No relay changes needed. No store changes needed. Works with both online and offline recipients (offline queueing handled by relay after nie-wneu.2).

Algorithm:
1. In cli/src/commands.rs in the user input handler (the block that checks line.strip_prefix for various /commands), add BEFORE the final broadcast send:

   if let Some(rest) = line.strip_prefix("/dm ") {
       let rest = rest.trim();
       let mut parts = rest.splitn(2, ' ');
       let handle = parts.next().unwrap_or("").trim();
       let text = parts.next().unwrap_or("").trim();
       if handle.is_empty() || text.is_empty() {
           println!("usage: /dm <handle> <text>");
           continue;
       }
       let peer = match resolve_handle(handle, &online, &nicknames, &local_names) {
           Some(p) => p,
           None => {
               println!("[dm] unknown: {handle}");
               continue;
           }
       };
       // For Phase 1 (pre-MLS), DMs are plaintext ClearMessage::Chat inside Whisper payload.
       // When mls_active, this will need per-peer MLS encryption (Phase 2 - nie-t4t).
       let payload = serde_json::to_vec(&ClearMessage::Chat { text: text.to_string() })
           // serde_json::to_vec on derived Serialize with only String fields cannot fail
           .unwrap();
       let req = JsonRpcRequest::new(
           next_request_id(),
           rpc_methods::WHISPER,
           WhisperParams { to: peer.clone(), payload },
       )?;
       tx.send(req).await?;
       let ts = Local::now().format("%H:%M");
       println!("\r[{ts}] DM → {}: {}", display_name(&peer, &nicknames, &local_names), text);
       continue;
   }

2. Add 'WhisperParams' and 'rpc_methods::WHISPER' to existing use imports if not already imported in this scope (check existing use statements at top of commands.rs).

Defensive rules:
- splitn(2, ' ') so message text with spaces is preserved as-is
- resolve_handle() handles: server nickname (/iam), local alias (/alias), pub_id prefix — reuse, do not re-implement
- The unwrap() on to_vec is justified: derived Serialize on struct with only String fields cannot fail — add comment
- Display with 'DM →' prefix on send confirmation so user can see it was routed as DM not broadcast

Tests:
- Unit test (can be doc-test or standalone): parse rest='alice hello world', verify handle='alice', text='hello world'
- Unit test: parse rest='alice' (no text), verify usage message (not panic)
- Serialize test: construct WhisperParams payload, deserialize as ClearMessage::Chat, assert text == original; oracle = serde_json roundtrip with known string
